We can rewrite the left side as one fraction using a common denominator. 
\begin{align*}
\frac 1{2!17!}+\frac 1{3!16!}+\frac 1{4!15!}+\frac 1{5!14!}+\frac 1{6!13!}+\frac 1{7!12!}+\frac 1{8!11!}+\frac 1{9!10!} &= \frac{17!+16!+15!+14!+13!+12!+11!+10!}{9!18!} \\
&= \frac{17!}{9!18!} \left(\frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{3\cdot16} + \frac{1}{4\cdot15} + \frac{1}{5\cdot14} + \frac{1}{6\cdot13} + \frac{1}{7\cdot12} + \frac{1}{8\cdot11} + \frac{1}{10}\right) \\
&= \frac{17!}{9!18!} \left(1 - \frac{1}{16!}\right) \\
&= \frac{17}{18} - \frac{17}{16!} \\
&= \frac{17}{18} - \frac{1}{16 \cdot 15!}
\end{align*}
This must be equal to $\frac{N}{1!18!}$, so comparing the two sides gives us $N = 17 - 1 = 16$. Therefore, the answer is $\boxed{16}$.
